@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Ballounes' where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have 8 colours or more.

                             How to play?

  Click on any balloon (the coloured circles) you want, this will burst
it and any balloon that have the same colour that is located next to it,
either horizontally or vertically, will also burst and so on. You will
get points according to the number of balloons that were eliminated, as
shown in the following table:

  2 balloons = 1 point
  3 balloons = 4 points
  4 balloons = 9 points 
  5 balloons = 16 points
  etc.

  If there are no balloons of the same colour that is next to the
balloon clicked on, two (2) new balloons will appear on the game board.
Do not let the board fill up completely because if it happens, the game
will be over.

  As the game progress, some of the following tiles will appear from
time to time:

 -Blocks:            Blocks do not serve any purpose other than being
                     there when you don't need them.

 -Bombs:             A Bomb (indicated by an 'explosion' icon) will
                     eliminate any tile that is located next to it,
                     either horizontally, vertically or diagonally. Any
                     tile removed will give you 1 point.

 -Lightning Tiles:   A Lightning tile (indicated by an 'electric flash'
                     icon), when clicked on, will generate lightning
                     bolts horizontally and vertically, eliminating any
                     tiles that are located in their paths. Each tile
                     eliminated will give you 1 point.

 -Mystery Tiles:     These tiles (indicated by a '?' symbol) will
                     randomly move up to 10 balloons on the board.

  The game keeps the best score made since the game was run.

  Have fun!

@endnode

